{
  "answer": "Drawing upon the profound wisdom found within the Final Revelation, which provides a steadfast foundation for the soul and a clear light of guidance, I identify the sacred *ayat* that anchor the linguistic structure of the *Shahada*. These verses illustrate the essential movement of the heart from the negation of all false deities (*Nafi*) to the unwavering affirmation of the Creator alone (*Ithbat*), ensuring a meaningful and enduring framework for the believer\u2019s journey.\n\n### **The Verbatim Formula of Oneness**\n\n**S\u016brah Muhammad (47:19)**\n*   **Arabic Text:** \u0641\u064e\u0627\u0639\u0652\u0644\u064e\u0645\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0644\u064e\u0627 \u0625\u0650\u0644\u064e\u0670\u0647\u064e \u0625\u0650\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f\n*   **English Translation:** \"So know, [O Muhammad], that there is no deity except God...\" [1].\n*   **Note:** This verse provides the definitive linguistic structure of the *Shahada*, commanding the believer to first negate the existence of any rival deity (*La ilaha*) before firmly affirming the exclusive right of Allah to be worshipped (*illAllah*) [1].\n\n---\n\n### **The Prophetic Pattern of Disassociation and Devotion**\n\n**S\u016brah az-Zukhruf (43:26-27)**\n*   **Arabic Text:** \u0648\u064e\u0625\u0650\u0630\u0652 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0625\u0650\u0628\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0627\u0647\u0650\u064a\u0645\u064f \u0644\u0650\u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0642\u064e\u0648\u0652\u0645\u0650\u0647\u0650 \u0625\u0650\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0646\u0650\u064a \u0628\u064e\u0631\u064e\u0627\u0621\u064c \u0645\u0650\u0651\u0645\u0651\u064e\u0627 \u062a\u064e\u0639\u0652\u0628\u064f\u062f\u064f\u0648\u0646\u064e . \u0625\u0650\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0630\u0650\u064a \u0641\u064e\u0637\u064e\u0631\u064e\u0646\u0650\u064a \u0641\u064e\u0625\u0650\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0633\u064e\u064a\u064e\u0647\u0652\u062f\u0650\u064a\u0646\u0650\n*   **English Translation:** \"And [mention, O Muhammad], when Abraham said to his father and his people, 'Indeed, I am disassociated from that which you worship (26) Except for He who created me; and indeed, He will guide me' (27)\" [2].\n*   **Note:** These verses echo the *Shahada\u2019s* structure through the example of Prophet Abraham, who established faith by first negating all false objects of worship through disassociation (*Nafi*) and then affirming his devotion to the One Creator (*Ithbat*) [2, 3].\n\n---\n\n**A Synthesis of Scriptural Guidance**\nThe linguistic structure of \"La ilaha illAllah\" is a \"trustworthy handhold with no break in it,\" requiring the soul to actively purge the heart of worldly attachments before it can truly receive the light of Divine guidance [4, 5]. As scholarly insights within the sources indicate, true righteousness is not merely a verbal profession but a lived reality where the negation of evil and the affirmation of God\u2019s sovereignty are seamlessly integrated into every action [6, 7]. \n\n***\n\n*Note: The Arabic text for these verses is provided from standard knowledge to fulfill the request for verbatim text, as the primary source material contains only the English translations.*",
